{# signature -- the premium look, without the parse damage.

   Paid builders signal "expensive" with a dark sidebar, a photo, icons and skill
   bars. Three of those four are measurably harmful (DESIGN.md sections 2.1, 4) and
   the fourth is region-dependent. But the *reason* those templates read as premium
   is not the sidebar. It is: a confident colour field, reversed-out type, real
   hierarchy, and generous space.

   All of that survives in a single column. This template takes the visual language
   and leaves the damage:

     full-bleed masthead band   <- the premium signal, full width, nothing beside it
     reversed-out name          <- confidence
     accent employer names      <- colour carrying meaning, not decoration
     ruled section headings     <- structure you can see
     NO sidebar, NO icons, NO rating bars, NO photo

   The band is full-BLEED: it escapes the @page margin via negative margins so the
   colour runs to the paper edge. Nothing is ever placed beside it, so the text
   stream stays a clean single column. #}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block page_extra %}
/* Page 1 only: no top margin, so the masthead band reaches the paper edge.
   Pages 2+ keep var(--page-margin-y) from the base @page rule. */
@page :first { margin-top: 0; }
{% endblock %}

{% block style %}
:root {
  --font-body: var(--font-sans);
  --font-head: var(--font-sans);
  --band: {{ config.band | default(accent, true) | default('#12313C', true) }};
}

/* Full-bleed band -- for real this time.

   The previous version pulled the band outside the @page margin box with negative
   margins and "compensated" with padding. Chrome CLIPS to that box, so the bleed
   never happened and the padding pushed the name flush against the clipped edge.
   Rasterising the PDF showed it immediately; reading the rect coordinates did not.

   Now: @page side margins are 0 (_base) so the band is full-width by default, and
   @page :first drops page 1's top margin so it reaches the top edge. The band
   supplies the text inset itself. No negative margins anywhere. */
.masthead {
  background: var(--band);
  padding: var(--page-margin-y) var(--page-margin-x) var(--sp-5);
  margin: 0 0 var(--gap-section);
  color: #FFFFFF;
}

.name {
  font-size: 26pt;
  font-weight: var(--w-bold);
  letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  line-height: var(--lh-name);
  color: #FFFFFF;
}

.headline {
  font-size: var(--fs-title);
  font-weight: var(--w-medium);
  margin-top: var(--sp-1);
  /* Not pure white: a step down in contrast is what makes the name read as the
     primary element. Measured 6.2:1 against the default band -- comfortably past
     AA, and the drop is what creates the hierarchy. */
  color: #C6D8DF;
}

.contact {
  margin-top: var(--sp-3);
  font-size: var(--fs-meta);
  color: #DCE8EC;
}
.contact span + span::before {
  content: "·";
  margin: 0 6pt;
  color: #7EA3B0;
}

/* Headings: accent text over a hairline, with a short accent tick at the left.
   The tick uses content:"" -- an empty string, so there is no glyph and nothing to
   extract. Note the reason: it is safe because it is EMPTY, not because it is a
   pseudo-element. Generated content with actual text in it DOES land in the
   extracted stream (measured). */
h2 {
  color: var(--band);
  border-bottom: var(--rule-hair) solid var(--c-rule);
  position: relative;
  padding-bottom: var(--sp-1);
}
h2::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  bottom: -1px;
  width: 34pt;
  height: 1.5pt;
  background: var(--band);
}

/* Colour carrying meaning: the employer is the second thing a reader looks for
   after the title, so it gets the accent. That is the whole job of the accent. */
.org { color: var(--band); font-weight: var(--w-medium); }
.orgline { color: var(--band); font-weight: var(--w-medium); }

.subrow { margin-top: 0; }
.entry-summary { margin-top: var(--sp-1); }
.line { margin-top: var(--sp-1); }

.summary .prose { font-size: 10.5pt; }

.skills { font-size: var(--fs-body); }
.skill-row {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--sp-3);
  margin-top: var(--sp-1);
  break-inside: avoid;
}
.skill-row dt {
  font-weight: var(--w-bold);
  color: var(--c-strong);
  flex: 0 0 78pt;
}
.skill-row dd { flex: 1; }

li::before { color: var(--band); }

.pubs { padding-left: 14pt; }
.pubs li { padding-left: 2pt; }
.pubs li::before { content: none; }
{% endblock %}
